  "title" : "How to convert / cast long to String?",
  "body" : "<p>I just created sample BB app, which can allow to choose the date.</p>\n\n<pre><code>DateField curDateFld = new DateField(\"Choose Date: \",\n  System.currentTimeMillis(), DateField.DATE | DateField.FIELD_LEFT);\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>After choosing the date, I need to convert that long value to String, so that I can easily store the date value somewhere in database.\nI am new to Java and Blackberry development.</p>\n\n<pre><code>long date = curDateFld.getDate();\n</code></pre>\n\n<p>How should I convert this long value to String? Also I want to convert back to long from String. I think for that I can use <code>long l = Long.parseLong(\"myStr\");</code>?</p>\n"
}